%3Cp%3EEven%20just%20strapping%20a%20grenade%20launcher%20to%20a%20rifle%20is%20nothing%20new%20%E2%80%93%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fspecial-ops.org%2Fm203-under-barrel-grenade-launcher%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EM203%20single-shot%20grenade%20launcher%20attachment%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20M16%20and%20M4%20has%20served%20for%20decades.%20However%2C%20the%20difference%20between%20the%20M203%20and%20advanced%20grenade%20launchers%20is%20substantial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20advanced%20launchers%20use%20smaller%20grenades%20that%20vary%20between%2020mm%20to%2035mm%3B%20further%2C%20they%20are%20not%20single-shot%20designs%20%E2%80%93%20which%20have%20been%20falling%20out%20of%20favor.%20Additionally%2C%20their%20grenades%20are%20not%20necessarily%20arced%20toward%20the%20target%20but%20rather%20aimed%20directly%20and%20propelled%20more%20like%20a%20traditional%20bullet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20common%20feature%20the%20latest%20systems%20offer%20is%20airburst.%20This%20allows%20the%20user%20to%20set%20the%20range%20at%20which%20the%20grenade%20will%20explode%2C%20meaning%20it%20is%20not%20reliant%20on%20striking%20something%20hard%20to%20detonate%3B%20this%20makes%20it%20extremely%20easy%20to%20eliminate%20threats%20behind%20cover.%20If%20you%20have%20an%20enemy%20at%20200%20yards%20behind%20a%20wall%20or%20in%20compounds%2C%20you%20can%20program%20the%20grenade%20to%20detonate%20at%20201%20meters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20soldier%20can%20then%20fire%20them%20over%20the%20top%20of%20the%20wall%2C%20and%20as%20the%20grenade%20passes%2C%20it%20explodes.%20Explosive%20fragmentation%20eliminates%20the%20enemy%2C%20and%20the%20soldiers%20move%20on.%20The%20grenade%20launcher%20can%20still%20likely%20punch%20through%20the%20cover%20faster%20than%20small%20arms%20fire%2C%20and%20while%20it%20is%20more%20lethal%20to%20the%20enemy%2C%20collateral%20damage%20is%20less%20likely%20due%20to%20the%20ease%20of%20detonation%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224af9c95d-cc2e-4d14-9ab0-9088f665232e%5C%22%3EEarly%20Western%20and%20Soviet%20efforts%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225564%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20diagram%20of%20a%20Soviet%20Kalashnikov%20AK-47%20assault%20rifle.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b4f8cf5da406397bf43ba4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222844%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20diagram%20of%20a%20Soviet%20Kalashnikov%20AK-47%20assault%20rifle.%3Cp%3EBettmann%2FContributor%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Carl%20Gustaf%20company%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20to%20experiment%20with%20the%20concept%20of%20combining%20a%20rifle%20with%20another%20firearm.%20Carl%20Gustaf%20created%20the%20NIVA%20XM1970%20in%201970%2C%20and%20it%20was%20not%20a%20grenade%20launcher%20but%20rather%20a%20regular%20rifle%20combined%20with%20a%20recoilless%2045mm%20one.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20rough%20design%2C%20the%20NIVA%20XM1970%20mounted%20over%20the%20shoulder%20like%20a%20recoilless%20rifle%2C%20and%20its%20stock%20allowed%20you%20to%20brace%20the%20gun%20against%20the%20shoulder.%20The%20recoilless%20rifle%20offered%20light%20anti-armor%20and%20anti-bunker%20capabilities.%20The%20rifle%20system%20was%20a%205.56mm%20that%20functioned%20as%20a%20bullpup.%20Its%20overall%20length%20was%20only%2035.4%20inches%20and%20it%20weighed%2011.9%20pounds.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20Iron%20Curtain%2C%20in%201975%2C%20the%20Soviets%20combined%20the%20AK-74%20platform%20with%20a%20small%2012.7mm%20grenade%20launcher.%20The%20gun%20had%20adjacent%20barrels%20and%20the%20grenade%20launcher%20was%20built%20into%20its%20left%20side.%20The%20grenade%20launcher%20featured%20a%2010-round%20magazine%20beside%20the%20AK's%2030-round%205.45%20magazine.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%2012.7mm%20grenade%20is%20relatively%20small%2C%20so%20fragmentation%20would%20be%20minimal%20but%20still%20likely%20offer%20excellent%20penetration%20through%20light%20armor%20and%20barriers%20at%20close%20range.%20Not%20much%20is%20known%20about%20the%20design%2C%20and%20it%20was%20never%20produced%20beyond%20the%20prototype%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22938f747f-e8cf-4525-9aec-11a34cd2397d%5C%22%3EThe%20PAPOP%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223096%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20soldier%20aims%20with%20a%20PAPOP%20modular%20weapon%20system%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b4fa07b4912df3ae1a033d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222027%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20soldier%20aims%20with%20a%20PAPOP%20modular%20weapon%20system.%3Cp%3EXavier%20Rossi%2FGamma-Rapho%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHave%20you%20ever%20watched%20a%20cheap%20science%20fiction%20movie%20and%20seen%20what%20looks%20like%20a%20chunk%20of%20plastic%20imitating%20a%20weapon%3F%20That's%20what%20I%20think%20of%20when%20I%20see%20the%20French%20PAPOP%3B%20the%20PAPOP-1%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20seems%20to%20be%20very%20awkward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20French%20designed%20the%20system%20in%201995%20by%20combining%20a%205.56%20caliber%20bullpup%20rifle%20with%20a%2035mm%20grenade%20launcher.%20The%20grenade%20launcher%20had%20a%20tube-fed%20design%2C%20much%20like%20a%20traditional%20shotgun.%20It%20was%20semi-automatic%20and%20carried%20three%20grenades%20at%20a%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20weapon%20featured%20programmable%20airburst%20shells%20and%20its%20aiming%20system%20was%20incredibly%20advanced%20using%20a%20rotating%20LCD%20screen%20and%20featuring%20night%20vision%2C%20a%20laser%20telemeter%2C%20a%20friend-or-foe%20identification%20tool%2C%20and%20a%20targeting%20computer%20to%20program%20grenades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20PAPOP-2%20reduced%20bolt%20and%20simplified%20the%20design%20but%20did%20not%20do%20enough%20to%20keep%20the%20system%20from%20being%20canceled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221f476bc3-4bd2-4a09-950b-d11d8e4aebe5%5C%22%3EXM29%20Objective%20Individual%20Combat%20Weapon%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222178%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20standard%205.56mm%20shell%20is%20displayed%20next%20to%2020mm%20airburst%20shell%20used%20in%20the%20XM29.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b4f482955b01c3294cf04d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221557%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20standard%205.56mm%20shell%20is%20displayed%20next%20to%2020mm%20airburst%20shell%20used%20in%20the%20XM29.%3Cp%3EStar%20Tribune%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Americans%20produced%20the%20XM29%20in%201996.%20Running%20until%202004%2C%20it%20was%20one%20of%20the%20longest-lasting%20programs%20%E2%80%93%20and%20an%20offshoot%20of%20the%20program%20even%20saw%20combat%20in%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20XM29%20series%20combined%20a%205.56%20rifle%20designed%20by%20HK%20with%20a%2020mm%20semi-automatic%2C%20magazine-fed%20grenade%20launcher.%20It%20featured%20a%20computerized%20sighting%20system%20that%20allowed%20the%20soldier%20to%20program%20the%2020mm%20grenades%20to%20airburst.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sighting%20system%20also%20offered%20a%20laser%20rangefinder%2C%20thermal%20capability%2C%20and%20a%206X%20optic%20sight.%20The%20Army%20envisioned%20the%20system%20as%20a%20counter-defilade%20weapon%20and%20a%20replacement%20for%20the%20M16.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20problems%20were%20discovered%20in%20testing%3A%20The%205.56%20rifle's%209.5-inch%20barrel%20generated%20pitiful%20velocity%20and%20had%20poor%20range%20while%20the%2020x28mm%20grenades%20didn't%20offer%20the%20best%20fragmentation%20range.%20Further%2C%20the%20weapon%20was%20heavy%2C%20bulky%2C%20and%20expensive.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20weapon%20system%20was%20split%20into%20three%20groups%2C%20including%20a%20stand-alone%20rifle%20and%20a%20grenade%20launcher%20%E2%80%94%20the%20XM25%20%E2%80%94%20which%20fired%20a%20larger%2025x40mm%20grenade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETroops%20in%20Afghanistan%20appreciated%20the%20weapon%2C%20but%20each%20round%20cost%20%241%2C000%20and%20had%20to%20be%20handmade.%20Plans%20were%20made%20to%20order%20more%2C%20but%20budget%20cuts%20prevented%20the%20program%20from%20moving%20onward.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dc9bb775-246e-4d4d-acbd-45dec8f43f67%5C%22%3EAdvanced%20Individual%20Combat%20Weapon%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225061%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20Australian%20Army%20soldier%20has%20his%20finger%20near%20the%20trigger%20of%20a%20F88%20Austeyr%20assault%20rifle.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b4fb99955b01c3294cf579%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223459%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20Australian%20Army%20soldier%20has%20his%20finger%20near%20the%20trigger%20of%20a%20F88%20Austeyr%20assault%20rifle.%3Cp%3EScott%20Barbour%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202001%2C%20Australia's%20Capability%20and%20Technology%20Demonstrator%20teamed%20up%20with%20DTSO%2C%20Metal%20Storm%2C%20and%20Tenix%20Defence%20Systems%20to%20produce%20a%20rifle%20and%20combination%20grenade%20launcher.%20The%20idea%20was%20to%20allow%20infantrymen%20to%20fire%20multiple%20grenades%20without%20having%20to%20reload%2C%20so%20the%20team%20combined%20the%20F88%20Austeyr%20with%20a%2040mm%20tube-loaded%2C%20three-shot%20grenade%20launcher%20to%20create%20the%20Advanced%20Individual%20Combat%20Weapon.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20grenade%20launcher%20used%20caseless%20ammo%2C%20which%20simplified%20the%20design%20because%20the%20ejection%20of%20a%20spent%20casing%20wasn't%20required.%20The%20user%20could%20load%20grenades%20much%20like%20a%20shotgun.%20Although%20the%20system%20lacked%20smart%20grenade%20capability%2C%20it%20did%20succeed%20in%20its%20objective.%20Unfortunately%2C%20it%20weighed%2022%20pounds%20loaded%20with%20the%20sighting%20system.%20The%20program%20was%20cut%20shortly%20after%20development%20was%20completed.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220b4074f6-9167-447e-a35d-c681fbb9b05a%5C%22%3EKorea's%20S%26amp%3BT%20Daewoo%20K11%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22S%26amp%3BT%20Daewoo%20K11%20Dual-barrel%20Air-burst%20Weapon%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b4f5ef955b01c3294cf143%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22680%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20S%26amp%3BT%20Daewoo%20K11%20Dual-barrel%20Airburst%20Weapon%20used%20a%20combination%20of%20a%205.56%20rifle%20with%20a%2020x30mm%20grenade.%3Cp%3EWar%20Memorial%20of%20Korea%20Open%20Archives%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Korean%20S%26amp%3BT%20Daewoo%20K11%20DAW%20is%20the%20most%20successful%20advanced%20launcher%20design%20that's%20been%20created%20yet.%20The%20weapon's%20design%20process%20started%20in%202006%3B%20the%20weapon%20began%20evaluation%20in%20the%20same%20year%3B%20and%2C%20by%202010%2C%20it%20was%20being%20produced.%20S%26amp%3BT%20Daewoo%20K11%20DAW%20used%20a%20combination%20of%20a%205.56%20rifle%20with%20a%2020x30mm%20grenade.%20Its%20grenade%20launcher%20is%20capable%20of%20using%20standard%20and%20smart%20air-bursting%20grenades.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sighting%20system%20contains%20a%20laser%20rangefinder%20as%20well%20as%20a%20ballistic%20computer%20allowing%20the%20user%20to%20easily%20program%20the%20smart%20grenades%20to%20airburst.%20The%20scope%20can%20be%20linked%20to%20a%20goggle%20system%20with%20a%20digital%20display%20and%20provide%20a%20thermal%20imaging%20system.%20The%20grenade%20launcher%20is%20semi-automatic%20and%20can%20hold%20up%20to%20six%20grenades%20in%20a%20box%20magazine.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Koreans%20used%20a%20clever%20fire-selector%20system%20that%20allowed%20the%20user%20to%20swap%20between%20rifle%20and%20grenade%20launcher%20while%20using%20the%20same%20trigger.%20While%20I%20can't%20speak%20to%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20the%2020x30mm%20grenade%20launcher%2C%20the%20weapon%20has%20been%20successful.%20South%20Korea%20adopted%20the%20platform%20in%202008%2C%20and%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20purchased%2040%20K11s%20in%202010.%20Seven%20K11%20advanced%20launchers%20even%20went%20to%20Afghanistan.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20the%20platform%20suffered%20from%20setbacks%2C%20and%20while%20several%20fixes%20were%20implemented%20by%202019%2C%20the%20program%20was%20canceled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2292ee7064-93cf-4031-8624-240a5c73ae6d%5C%22%3ECold%20Canada's%20unnamed%20rifle%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Canadian%20Army%20solldiers%20test%20a%20protoype%20of%20the%20next%20generation%20rifle.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b4f6c6b4912df3ae1a0091%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECanadian%20Army%20soldiers%20test%20a%20prototype%20of%20the%20next%20generation%20rifle.%3Cp%3ECanadian%20Department%20of%20National%20Defense%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20Colt%20Canada%20and%20the%20Canadian%20military%20developed%20an%20unnamed%20rifle%20system%20that%20combined%20a%20rifle%20with%20a%20three-shot%2040mm%20grenade%20launcher%20that%20could%20be%20swapped%20for%20a%2012-gauge%20shotgun.%20There%20is%20no%20mention%20of%20air%20bursts%20or%20programmable%20grenades.%20The%20rifle%20is%20supposed%20to%20use%20cased%20telescopic%20ammo%2C%20but%20a%20caliber%20is%20not%20mentioned.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20even%20clear%20if%20the%20rifle%20was%20capable%20of%20firing%20or%20was%20just%20a%20mockup%20%E2%80%93%20although%2C%20based%20on%20the%20few%20photos%20that%20have%20been%20released%2C%20it%20probably%20wasn't%20fired.%20The%20program%20seems%20abandoned%2C%20and%20this%20crazy-looking%20weapon%20never%20moved%20forward.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20the%20above%20systems%20were%20compl