all%20its%20business%20lines%20to%20get%20permission%20to%20donate%20to%20Harris%2FWalz.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20is%20due%20to%20the%20SEC's%20%26quot%3Bpay-to-play%26quot%3B%20rule%20that%20restricts%20donating%20to%20state%20and%20local%20officials.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBanks%20and%20hedge%20funds%20face%20fines%20and%20compensation%20bans%20for%20even%20one-time%2C%20small-dollar%20donations.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20presidential%20election%2C%20Wall%20Street%20donors%20turned%20out%20for%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20contributing%20more%20than%20%2474%20million%20to%20his%202020%20campaign%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.opensecrets.org%2Fnews%2F2020%2F11%2Fbiden-wins%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECenter%20for%20Responsive%20Politics%20data%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20time%20around%2C%20Democrat-leaning%20bankers%20have%20their%20hands%20tied%20due%20to%20Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris'%20choice%20of%20running%20mate%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-leaders-respond-kamala-harris-selects-tim-walz-vp-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMinnesota%20Gov.%20Tim%20Walz%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Financial%20services%20firms%20risk%20the%20wrath%20of%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20if%20their%20employees%20make%20campaign%20contributions%20to%20state%20or%20local%20officials%20such%20as%20Walz.%20Donating%20to%20the%20campaign%20would%20violate%20the%20regulator's%20%26quot%3Bpay-to-play%26quot%3B%20rule%2C%20which%20keeps%20firms%20from%20trying%20to%20sway%20politicians%20for%20favors%20such%20as%20managing%20their%20state's%20pension%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20heed%20this%20rule%2C%20Citigroup%20told%20US%20employees%20on%20August%206%20that%20they%20must%20seek%20pre-approval%20to%20donate%20to%20the%20Harris-Walz%20campaign%2C%20according%20to%20a%20memo%20seen%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20These%20restrictions%20apply%20to%20employees%20who%20belong%20to%20all%20but%20one%20of%20its%20five%20business%20units%2C%20including%20investment%20banking%20and%20wealth%20management.%20The%20US%20consumer%20banking%20division%20is%20exempt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECiti%20employees%20are%20not%20required%20to%20get%20pre-approval%20to%20donate%20to%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20campaign%20unless%20they%20are%20designated%20as%20a%20%26quot%3BMunicipal%20Finance%20Professional%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BCovered%20Associate%26quot%3B%20or%20are%20part%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bpublic-sector%20facing%20business.%26quot%3B%20Those%20employees%20are%20also%20required%20to%20get%20permission%20to%20donate%20to%20the%20Harris-Walz%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SEC's%20%26quot%3Bpay%20to%20play%26quot%3B%20rule%2C%20adopted%20in%202010%2C%20also%20applies%20to%20Citi's%20peers%2C%20such%20as%20JPMorgan%2C%20Wells%20Fargo%2C%20and%20Bank%20of%20America%2C%20which%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20in%20time%20for%20publication.%20It%20is%20unclear%20whether%20those%20banks%20are%20asking%20employees%20for%20pre-approvals%20or%20banning%20contributions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECiti%20implemented%20a%20similar%20policy%20in%202016%20when%20Trump%20selected%20then-governor%20of%20Indiana%20Mike%20Pence%20as%20his%20running%20mate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20policies%20may%20seem%20harsh%2C%20but%20even%20small%20donations%20can%20incur%20steep%20penalties.%20In%202017%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpershing-square-and-other-funds-fined-by-sec-for-violating-pay-to-play-2017-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPershing%20Square%3C%2Fa%3E%20paid%20a%20%2475%2C000%20fine%20four%20years%20after%20a%20then-analyst%20donated%20%24500%20to%20a%20candidate%20for%20governor%20of%20Massachusetts.%20The%20state's%20pension%20plan%20was%20an%20investor%20in%20Pershing%20Square%20at%20the%20time.%20Pershing%20was%20unaware%20of%20the%20donation%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20said%20at%20the%20time%2C%20and%20the%20analyst%20was%20able%20to%20get%20his%20money%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SEC%20bars%20banks%20from%20getting%20paid%20for%20government%20advisory%20services%20for%20two%20years%20after%20donations%20to%20a%20state%20or%20local%20official.%20This%20applies%20to%20donations%20over%20%24350%20made%20by%20employees%20%3Cem%3Ebefore%3C%2Fem%3E%20they%20joined%20the%20bank.%20JPMorgan%20agreed%20to%20advise%20a%20Tallahassee%2C%20Florida%20pension%20fund%20for%20two%20years%20for%20free%20after%20hiring%20an%20employee%20who%20had%20previously%20donated%20to%20a%20mayoral%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20sort%20of%20single%20out%20one%20campaign%20over%20the%20other%2C%20whatever%20the%20reason%20is%20%E2%80%94%20and%20there's%20regulation%20in%20place%20there%20%E2%80%94%20it%20looks%20very%20political%2C%26quot%3B%20Professor%20Patricia%20Crouse%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECrouse%2C%20who%20teaches%20political%20science%20at%20the%20University%20of%20New%20Haven%2C%20said%20these%20policies%20inevitably%20discourage%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20support%20your%20candidates%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20you%20can't%20do%20that%2C%20I%20think%20it%20makes%20you%20feel%20left%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20possible%20to%20sidestep%20the%20%26quot%3Bpay%20to%20play%26quot%3B%20rule%20by%20donating%20to%20PACs%20or%20Super%20PACs%20that%20aren't%20directly%20tied%20to%20the%20relevant%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20then-SEC%20Commissioner%20Hester%20Peirce%20criticized%20the%20pay-to-play%20rule%20after%20the%20SEC%20fined%20four%20investment%20advisors%20for%20one-time%2C%20small%20donations%2C%20calling%20it%20an%20%26quot%3Bexceedingly%20blunt%20instrument.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Pay-to-Play%20Rule%2C%20although%20well-intentioned%2C%20imposes%20unique%2C%20unquantifiable%20costs%20on%20individuals%20by%20impeding%20their%20ability