0agencies%2C%20including%20the%20ED%2C%20to%20target%20political%20opponents.%20The%20BJP%20has%20denied%20the%20allegations%20and%20claimed%20that%20the%20ED%20is%20following%20the%20rule%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20observed%20that%20the%20ED%20needs%20to%20focus%20on%20the%20quality%20of%20prosecution%20and%20evidence%2C%20citing%20low%20conviction%20rates%20in%20cases%20under%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act.%20The%20observation%20came%20after%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20Home%20Nityanand%20Rai%20told%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20that%20more%20than%205%2C200%20money%20laundering%20cases%20had%20been%20registered%20by%20the%20ED%20since%202014%20and%20convictions%20were%20obtained%20in%2040.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723139400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-06%2Fdvh2eaio_v-senthil-balaji-_625x300_14_June_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcourt-frames-money-laundering-charges-against-ex-tamil-nadu-minister-senthil-balaji-6295343%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20special%20court%20in%20Chennai%20framed%20charges%20against%20former%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Minister%20V%20Senthil%20Balaji%20under%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20on%20Thursday%20in%20connection%20with%20an%20alleged%20cash-for-jobs%20scam.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BAsatya%2C%20Not%20Jhooth%26quot%3B%3A%20When%20Amit%20Shah%20Helped%20Out%20Kiren%20Rijiju%20In%20Parliament%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Opposition's%20ongoing%20objections%20about%20%26quot%3Bunparliamentary%26quot%3B%20language%20provided%20some%20lighter%20moments%20in%20parliament%20today%20amid%20the%20acrimonious%20discussion%20of%20the%20Waqf%20Amendment%20Bill.%20This%20time%2C%20Union%20minister%20Kiren%20Rijiju%20averted%20a%20pitfall%2C%20with%20some%20'help'%20from%20senior%20cabinet%20colleague%20Amit%20Shah.%20The%20Minister%20for%20Minority%20Affairs%20was%20responding%20to%20the%20debate%20on%20the%20bill%2C%20which%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20today%20amid%20a%20barrage%20of%20Opposition%20criticism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20why%20the%20government%20thought%20it%20fit%20to%20go%20ahead%20with%20the%20bill%2C%20he%20spoke%20of%20a%20Muslim%20woman%20from%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20directing%20a%20jibe%20at%20Samajwadi%20Party%20leader%20Akhilesh%20Yadav.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBushra%20Fathima...%20You%20were%20probably%20the%20Chief%20Minister%20then.%20Didn't%20anyone%20inform%20you%3F%20She%20is%20having%20such%20a%20difficult%20time%20trying%20to%20survive%20with%20her%20children.%20But%20if%20there%20is%20no%20change%20in%20Waqf%20laws%2C%20once%20her%20husband%20dies%2C%20the%20property%20will%20go%20to%20the%20Waqf%20board%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Rijiju%20said%2C%20holding%20her%20as%20a%20case%20study%20for%20the%20government's%20stance%20that%20a%20change%20in%20the%20current%20law%20would%20help%20women%20and%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmid%20cries%20of%20%26quot%3BShame%2C%20shame%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20treasury%20benches%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BShould%20we%20not%20intervene%20in%20such%20a%20situation%3F%20Should%20no%20step%20be%20taken%20to%20get%20her%20justice%3F%20Don't%20look%20at%20this%20through%20the%20prism%20of%20religion%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20Opposition%20benches%20started%20sounding%20like%20an%20angry%20beehive%2C%20the%20minister%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Congress%20people%20have%20this%20problem%20--%20they%20ask%20a%20question%20and%20when%20I%20try%20to%20clarify%20matters%2C%20they%20say%20'Form%20a%20committee'.%20Don't%20try%20to%20run%20off%20after%20raising%20an%20issue%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20cutting%20through%20more%20comments%20about%20JPC%20that%20floated%20in%2C%20Mr%20Rijiju%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20explained%20matters.%20On%20what%20will%20be%20done%2C%20Mr%20Speaker%2C%20we%20will%20move%20forward%20with%20your%20agreement%20and%20the%20sense%20of%20the%20House.%20But%20so%20many%20members%20spoke%20today%20of%20so%20many%20things%20at%20length%2C%20so%20many%20lies%20(%3Cem%3EJhooth%3C%2Fem%3E)%20%2C%20creating%20misconceptions...%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%2C%20interrupted%20by%20loud%20protests%2C%20he%20corrected%20himself%20and%20said%20%26quot%3Buntruths'%20(%3Cem%3EAsathya%3C%2Fem%3E).%20But%20that%20did%20not%20appear%20to%20pacify%20the%20Opposition.%20Amid%20the%20cacophony%2C%20Union%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20got%20up%20and%20declared%2C%20%26quot%3BDon't%20say%20lies%20(%3Cem%3Ejhooth%3C%2Fem%3E).%20Let's%20say%20they%20have%20not%20spoken%20the%20truth%26quot%3B.%20Even%20the%20Speaker%20was%20seen%20smiling%20broadly%20at%20the%20amendment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20woman%20member%2C%20presumably%20from%20the%20Opposition%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BSay%20untruths%20and%20misinformation%26quot%3B.%20Now%20Mr%20Rijiju%20grinned%20and%20in%20an%20approving%20tone%2C%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20do%20know%20untruths%20were%20said%20and%20misconception%20spread%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20building%20his%20case%20for%20the%20bill%2C%20Mr%20Rijiju%20had%20said%20that%20the%20law%20has%20been%20in%20the%20making%20for%20over%2010%20years%20and%20it%20was%20time%20to%20bite%20the%20bullet%20and%20do%20it.%20Even%20the%20Opposition%2C%20he%20said%2C%20knew%20it%20and%20approved%20of%20it%20in%20their%20hearts.%20%26quot%3BBut%20they%20cannot%20say%20so%20because%20of%20political%20reasons%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Citing%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%2C%20Congress's%20Rahul%20Gandhi%2C%20who%20had%20walked%20off%2C%20Mr%20Rijiju%20said%2C%20'He%20has%20given%20his%20approval%20before%20leaving%2C%26quot%3B%20bringing%20guffaws%20from%20his%20party%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Waqf%20Amendment%20Bill%2C%20which%20envisages%20changes%20to%20the%20existing%20version%20on%2044%20points%2C%20has%20been%20criticised%20as%20%26quot%3Bdraconian%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20Opposition%20parties.%20Many%20leaders%20have%20contended%20that%20it%20violates%20fundamental%20rights%20and%20ideas%20enshrined%20in%20the%20Constitution%2C%20including%20Article%2014%2C%20which%20guarantees%20equality%20before%20law%2C%20Article%2015%2C%20which%20bars%20discrimination%20on%20basis%20of%20religion%20and%20Article%2025%2C%20which%20guarantees%20religious%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20defended%20the%20Bill%20saying%20it%20would%20lead%20to%20transparency%20and%20benefits%20to%20women%20and%20children%20by%20protecting%20their%20inheritance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20requires%20that%20money%20received%20by%20the%20Waqf%20Board%20must%20be%20used%20for%20the%20welfare%20of%20widows%2C%20divorcees%2C%20and%20orphans%20in%20the%20manner%20suggested%20by%20the%20government.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723138800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fsoiftga8_kiren-rijiju_625x300_08_August_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fasatya-not-jhooth-when-amit-shah-helped-out-kiren-rijiju-in-parliament-6295308%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Opposition's%20ongoing%20objections%20about%20%26quot%3Bunparliamentary%26quot%3B%20language%20provided%20some%20lighter%20moments%20in%20parliament%20today%20amid%20the%20acrimonious%20discussion%20of%20the%20Waqf%20Amendment%20Bill.%20This%20time%2C%20Union%20minister%20Kiren%20Rijiju%20averted%20a%20pitfall%2C%20with%20some%20'he%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Highlights%3A%20Bangladesh%20Interim%20Government%2C%20Led%20By%20Muhammad%20Yunus%2C%20Takes%20Oath%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ENobel%20Peace%20Prize%20winner%20Muhamma